column1: Restraining  the  Respondents  from  blocking  access  to  the  College  by
padlocking  the  access  gates,  entering  the  premises  of  the  College,
threatening,  abusing  or  doing  any  act  that  impedes  or  obstructs  the
Petitioners  from  managing  and  administering  the  College.  Thereafter,
the  inquiry  pertaining  to  the  interim  injunction  was  resolved  as  the
Respondents permitted the Petitioners to carry on the administration of
the said College without any impediments.
